00:34:07.240 --> 00:34:07.440
Okay.

564
00:34:08.480 --> 00:34:12.140
I'll shift gears a bit now and talk about the

565
00:34:12.200 --> 00:34:14.361
NIH Data Management and Sharing Policy.

566
00:34:15.020 --> 00:34:17.091
NIH has had a long-standing

567
00:34:18.140 --> 00:34:22.020
commitment to openly making the

568
00:34:22.040 --> 00:34:23.960
results of NIH-funded results

569
00:34:24.600 --> 00:34:28.190
available. Responsible data management and

570
00:34:28.281 --> 00:34:32.071
sharing have many benefits like accelerating the

571
00:34:33.560 --> 00:34:37.540
pace of biomedical research, enabling validation of research

572
00:34:37.600 --> 00:34:38.740
results, and

573
00:34:39.560 --> 00:34:43.261
most importantly, providing access to high-value datasets.

574
00:34:43.801 --> 00:34:47.220
To promote sharing of scientific data, NIH issued

575
00:34:47.620 --> 00:34:51.060
the DMS, or the Data Management and Sharing Policy in

576
00:34:51.140 --> 00:34:55.019
2023. The policy seeks to promote a culture

577
00:34:55.060 --> 00:34:58.800
in which data management and sharing are an integral component of a

578
00:34:58.820 --> 00:35:02.580
biomedical research project, rather than an administrative or

579
00:35:02.660 --> 00:35:03.320
additive one.

580
00:35:04.920 --> 00:35:08.740
Data management and sharing practices should be consistent with the

581
00:35:08.780 --> 00:35:12.280
FAIR principles. Which is to say that your data should be

582
00:35:12.320 --> 00:35:15.780
findable, accessible, interoperable, and reusable.

583
00:35:16.800 --> 00:35:20.020
Hence, all research grants that generate scientific data

584
00:35:20.560 --> 00:35:23.700
must include a DMS plan, where investigators have

585
00:35:23.740 --> 00:35:27.510
prospectively planned on how to preserve and share scientific

586
00:35:27.600 --> 00:35:29.320
data with the scientific community.

587
00:35:31.240 --> 00:35:34.740
So what does that mean for you all when you're putting together your

588
00:35:34.780 --> 00:35:38.120
applications? So this is an overview, quick overview.

589
00:35:39.130 --> 00:35:42.880
Plan and budget for the managing and sharing of scientific data at the

590
00:35:42.920 --> 00:35:45.150
time of putting together your application.

591
00:35:46.020 --> 00:35:49.860
Submit a DMS plan that make your data findable, accessible,

592
00:35:50.020 --> 00:35:51.680
interoperable, and reusable.

593
00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:54.020
If you notice,

594
00:35:55.480 --> 00:35:57.800
in the simplified

595
00:35:59.000 --> 00:36:01.200
review process, there is no mention of DMS.

596
00:36:01.660 --> 00:36:05.280
DMS plans are not reviewed by the review

597
00:36:05.380 --> 00:36:08.380
panel while giving you your priority score.

598
00:36:09.580 --> 00:36:13.380
It is approved, the plans are approved by your NCI

599
00:36:13.460 --> 00:36:16.940
program director. However, awards will not be

600
00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:20.600
made until an appropriate DMS plan is received and

601
00:36:20.640 --> 00:36:23.220
approved by the program director.

602
00:36:24.580 --> 00:36:28.520
And once approved, you have to comply with the plan for

603
00:36:28.540 --> 00:36:31.020
the period of the award. And progress of

604
00:36:32.220 --> 00:36:36.160
your data sharing is reported yearly in the

605
00:36:36.200 --> 00:36:38.380
Research Performance Progress Report, or the

606
00:36:38.460 --> 00:36:42.752
RPPRNIH

607
00:36:43.772 --> 00:36:47.492
highly encourages and recommends maximum data sharing.

608
00:36:48.592 --> 00:36:52.132
However, data sharing limitations due to ethical,

609
00:36:52.252 --> 00:36:53.882
legal, and technical factors

610
00:36:54.952 --> 00:36:58.862
is possible, and those limitations must be described in

611
00:36:58.912 --> 00:37:00.252
the DMS plan.

612
00:37:02.532 --> 00:37:05.932
Protecting the privacy of human research participants is

613
00:37:05.952 --> 00:37:09.812
paramount, and hence, responsible data sharing of

614
00:37:09.872 --> 00:37:13.652
human research subjects is expected, keeping in mind

615
00:37:14.172 --> 00:37:15.812
this expectation.

616
00:37:17.792 --> 00:37:21.411
NIH recommends again, highly, to share

617
00:37:21.632 --> 00:37:23.572
data in established repositories.

618
00:37:24.412 --> 00:37:28.252
And there are many domain-specific NIH-supported

619
00:37:28.312 --> 00:37:31.712
repositories out there. However, if you cannot

620
00:37:31.852 --> 00:37:35.572
find a domain-specific repository for your data

621
00:37:35.652 --> 00:37:36.392
type or

622
00:37:37.312 --> 00:37:38.192
an established

623
00:37:39.072 --> 00:37:42.952
repository for your data type, a generalist repository would be a

624
00:37:43.012 --> 00:37:44.272
good alternative

625
00:37:45.712 --> 00:37:47.012
to pursue.

